# ───────────────────────── secrets / env ─────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*-keypair.json
**/keypairs/*.json
!**/keypairs/.gitkeep
# Defense-in-depth: never commit a key directory (spike funds, deploy authority, …).
**/.keys/

# ──────────────── internal / idea-phase artifacts (not public) ────────────────
# Idea-discovery output + agent session state — kept locally, never pushed.
.superstack/
.claude/
report-payload.json
idea-shortlist-*.html
idea-deep-dive-*.html
# Detailed pre-mainnet security audit — kept private (it spells out a fixed exploit + an
# ER-SDK root cause that affects other teams; responsible disclosure). The public README
# carries only the high-level "audited, found+fixed a critical, proven by tests" summary.
**/SECURITY-AUDIT.md
.gstack/security-reports/

# Internal working docs — not needed in the public repo (planning / spikes / research / version pins).
docs/UI-BUILD-PLAN.md
docs/FEASIBILITY.md
docs/M0-SPIKE-RESULTS.md
docs/VERSIONS.md
docs/research/

# Agent tooling + scratch
.agents/
skills-lock.json
# tmp/

# ───────────────────────── rust / anchor ─────────────────────────
programs/**/target/
target/
**/*.rs.bk
.anchor/
test-ledger/
**/Cargo.lock        # libraries: keep unlocked; the deployable program pins via toolchain
!programs/**/Cargo.lock   # the program is a binary artifact: DO lock it

